# Svelte / SvelteKit Development Guide

## Svelte Version

- **Svelte 5 is mandatory**: All code must target and use Svelte 5. Do not use older Svelte versions for any new development or refactoring.

## Code Snippets

- **Snippets are for small components only**:
  - Use snippets exclusively for trivial or frequently reused UI fragments or micro-components.
  - For anything larger or more complex, create a dedicated, clearly named Svelte component file instead.
  - Avoid snippet-based patterns for logic-heavy components, pages, or layouts.

## Component Library Use

- **Shadcn usage is required wherever possible**:
  - Use [shadcn/ui](https://ui.shadcn.com) components for all standard UI primitives (buttons, inputs, dialogs, etc.).
  - Only create custom UI components if there isn't a suitable shadcn component.
  - When using shadcn components, follow shadcn best practices for customization and theming.

## Internationalization

- **All texts must be translated using @deckweiss/internationalization**:
  - Use the `@deckweiss/internationalization` package for all text translations in Svelte components.
  - Never hardcode text strings directly in components - always use the internationalization package.
  - Follow the package's API and best practices for translation keys and usage.

## Data Loading

- **Use SvelteKit remote functions when loading data**:
  - Always use SvelteKit remote functions (server-side functions) for data loading operations.
  - Prefer remote functions over direct API calls or client-side data fetching when possible.
  - Follow SvelteKit best practices for remote function implementation and error handling.
